      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And I will give him rest from all his enemies round about—i.e., the surrounding peoples, who are his natural foes, seeing that they were brought under the yoke by his father, will acquiesce in his dominion. The same words are used, in a somewhat different sense. about David (2Samuel 7:1); and in 1Kings 5:4 Solomon applies them to himself. (Comp. also Proverbs 16:7.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And I will give him rest from all his enemies round",
            "children": []
