            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) The Hebrew is ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Shĕlōmō;",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " for which the LXX. gives Sălōmōn; Syriac, Shĕleimûn; Arabic, Suleimân (same as “Solyman the Magnificent”). The original form of the word had the final ",
